sightings.description: A heard of elephants was seen near village farms,causing concern among residents due to possible crop destruction.
A hippo emerged from the lake at dusk, damaging fishing nets and scaring locals fetching water.
A herd of zebras entered grazing land, competing with livestock for pasture during the dry season.
A crocodile was spotted near the ferry landing, causing fear among fishermen and river users.
Villagers reported a leopard near goat sheds, prompting wildlife officers to patrol the area.
A lone buffalo strayed close to cattle grazing areas, forcing herders to relocate their animals temporarily.
Residents spotted a hippo grazing near the riverbank, blocking access to water points used by villagers.
